@startuml
' Filename: Sensor_Ingress_Sequence_Diagram.plantuml
' Diagram Type: Sequence Diagram
' Authored 2026-07-18 from src/simulation/external-sense-ingress.ts,
' docs/infrastructure/SENSOR_INGRESS.md, docs/infrastructure/SENSOR_PAGE.md.
' The phygital sensor path: a /sensor client streams a normalized light level
' that superposes onto a unit's receiver, then the normal decode pipeline runs.

participant "/sensor client\n(camera + detector)" as Client
participant "Simulation Server\n(scripts/simulation-server.mjs)" as Server
participant "ExternalSenseLatch\n(external-sense-ingress.ts)" as Latch
participant "Engine seam\nsetExternalSenseLevel" as Engine
participant "Environment\n(lightPulseInput merge)" as Env
participant "Receiver decode\n(<unit>/receiver)" as Decode

' Client armed only after an explicit Start / All on.
' Capture rides requestAnimationFrame, so streaming pauses while the tab is hidden.
loop every rAF frame while armed (~20 Hz), per mapping
    Client -> Client : capture frame -> BT.601 zone luminance\ndelta vs threshold -> normalize level 0..1
    Client -> Server : sensor_input { unit, channel, level, seq, sampleTimestamp }

    alt (unit, channel) not declared by loaded package
        Server --> Client : error SENSOR_NOT_BOUND
    else level non-finite or negative
        Server --> Client : error SENSOR_LEVEL_INVALID
    else dist helpers missing
        Server --> Client : error SENSOR_INGRESS_UNAVAILABLE
    else socket lacks operator capability
        Server --> Client : error NOT_AUTHORIZED
    else accepted
        ' latest-wins latch, keyed unit:channel; nothing queues.
        ' Staleness is judged later at drain time, by server receive time.
        Server -> Latch : set(unit, channel, { level, receivedAtMs, seq, owner })
        ' No per-sample ack on success (the stream is high-rate).
    end
end

' Independent cadence: the tick loop drains the latch once per binding, per tick,
' immediately before sim.step(1) (top of the else-if(sim) branch -> never in replay).
loop every simulation tick, per binding (drainExternalSense)
    Server -> Latch : get(unit, channel)
    Latch --> Server : latest sample (or none)
    alt fresh: age <= stalenessTicks x TICK_MS
        Server -> Server : calibrate level = max(0, gain*level + offset)
        Server -> Engine : setExternalSenseLevel(unit, channel, level, mode)
    else stale or absent
        ' null RELEASES the channel back to geometry, never to zero.
        Server -> Engine : setExternalSenseLevel(unit, channel, null, mode)
    end

    alt unit has an authored light sensor (else no-op: no eye, no sight)
        Engine -> Env : lightPulseInput(level, mode)
        alt mode = sum
            Env -> Env : merged = geometric + external
        else mode = replace
            Env -> Env : merged = external
        end
        Env -> Decode : sense_light_level = merged
        ' The unit's own decode pipeline is untouched - torch is decoded like a NeoPixel ring.
        Decode -> Decode : rolling background -> internal_light_background
        Decode -> Decode : delta vs authored sensitivity -> internal_light_delta
        Decode -> Decode : is-pulse bit -> internal_light_is_pulse
        Decode -> Decode : 40-sample word correlation ->\ninternal_received_word / internal_word_distance
    end

    Server -> Server : sim.step(1) advances the frame
end

' Client observes the loop close via the patch stream (round-trip graph),
' reading behavioral.frame.values at <unit>/receiver.
Server --> Client : behavioral frame patch\n(sense_light_level, internal_light_is_pulse, internal_received_word)

legend right
  Source: src/simulation/external-sense-ingress.ts (latch/drain arithmetic),
  docs/infrastructure/SENSOR_INGRESS.md, docs/infrastructure/SENSOR_PAGE.md.
  Wire: type snake_case, envelope fields camelCase; replies only on error.
  No new frame-variable keys - the merged level flows through the EXISTING
  receiver lanes: sense_light_level, internal_light_background /
  internal_light_delta / internal_light_is_pulse, internal_received_word /
  internal_word_distance. Per-sensor sense_signal glyph lanes stay geometric.
  Binding fields (variables.externalSensors): unit, channel (light|sound),
  mode (sum|replace), gain, offset, stalenessTicks (defaults in
  EXTERNAL_SENSE_DEFAULTS). Auth: sensor_input rides the canControl operator
  capability. null fails back to GEOMETRY, never to zero.
endlegend

@enduml
